ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this course to any student of literature or anyone interested in how to read different texts together and without eliding their differences find the points of contact. It is also excellent to see a sharp analytic mind discuss complex issues in precise terms.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course deepened and changed my understanding what could be called anti-humanism in literature, not only a political but also an aesthetic issue of interest to me and a possible component of my dissertation.
